HEADWORD: Thorough bass
<hw>Thor"ough bass`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>The
representation of chords by figures placed under the base; figured bass;
basso continuo; -- sometimes used as synonymous with
<altname>harmony</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

